01:01:36,330 --> 01:01:37,460
You don't get it.

1756
01:01:37,890 --> 01:01:39,059
You should say something...

1757
01:01:39,060 --> 01:01:40,459
for us to get anything.

1758
01:01:40,460 --> 01:01:43,800
If you hadn't unbuckled and stayed there, we'd have won.

1759
01:01:43,830 --> 01:01:47,099
The food should be ready when the rider comes.

1760
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:48,870
Hey, the order is...

1761
01:01:51,140 --> 01:01:52,140
Hold on.

1762
01:01:52,141 --> 01:01:54,010
(I've had enough of this!)

1763
01:01:54,710 --> 01:01:55,710
Hey!

1764
01:01:56,180 --> 01:01:58,250
(The vicious delivery showdown)

1765
01:01:59,620 --> 01:02:01,750
(The opponent was too strong!)

1766
01:02:02,550 --> 01:02:04,150
Darn it. You come here.

1767
01:02:04,420 --> 01:02:06,289
(Backing down)

1768
01:02:06,290 --> 01:02:08,389
- Come here.
- I'm sorry.

1769
01:02:08,390 --> 01:02:09,559
- You punk.
- I'm sorry.

1770
01:02:09,560 --> 01:02:10,729
Speak now.

1771
01:02:10,730 --> 01:02:12,629
- I'm sorry.
- This isn't your first time, is it?

1772
01:02:12,630 --> 01:02:13,729
- This isn't your first time, is it?
- I'm sorry.

1773
01:02:13,730 --> 01:02:15,970
Why aren't you delivering our food properly?

1774
01:02:16,230 --> 01:02:17,370
Why?

1775
01:02:17,930 --> 01:02:19,599
- Are you a high school student?
- I'm sorry.

1776
01:02:19,600 --> 01:02:21,640
- Are you a high school student?
- Yes.

1777
01:02:21,740 --> 01:02:23,586
Don't come to deliver our food. Do you understand?

1778
01:02:23,610 --> 01:02:24,639
Darn it.

1779
01:02:24,640 --> 01:02:25,879
(It turns out he was a high school rider.)

1780
01:02:25,880 --> 01:02:28,110
- I'm sorry.
- You're messing with our work.

1781
01:02:28,410 --> 01:02:30,509
People keep calling us.

1782
01:02:30,510 --> 01:02:31,850
I'm sorry.

1783
01:02:31,920 --> 01:02:33,150
What happened, Se Yoon?

1784
01:02:33,650 --> 01:02:35,089
- What?
- What happened?

1785
01:02:35,090 --> 01:02:36,120
(He's curious.)

1786
01:02:36,620 --> 01:02:37,820
- Director Joo.
- Yes.

1787
01:02:40,020 --> 01:02:41,930
(Being humble)

1788
01:02:42,360 --> 01:02:43,930
Say you're sorry.

1789
01:02:44,330 --> 01:02:46,529
It's my fault for not educating my brothers.

1790
01:02:46,530 --> 01:02:47,829
Our eldest brother is waiting over there,

1791
01:02:47,830 --> 01:02:49,270
thinking our business is doing well.

1792
01:02:49,870 --> 01:02:52,070
- He's excited.
- Aren't you going to do business?

1793
01:02:53,140 --> 01:02:54,870
I think he should get fired.

1794
01:02:55,510 --> 01:02:56,639
He's so slow.

1795
01:02:56,640 --> 01:02:59,080
"Hamburger, cheese!"

1796
01:02:59,280 --> 01:03:00,909
Should one of us be the head chef?

1797
01:03:00,910 --> 01:03:02,709
- Can't DinDin go?
- No. Listen.

1798
01:03:02,710 --> 01:03:05,149
We have to leave it to him now.

1799
01:03:05,150 --> 01:03:07,079
- But Jong Min...
- He's done it before.

1800
01:03:07,080 --> 01:03:09,419
Ask a few more times...

1801
01:03:09,420 --> 01:03:11,189
to memorize the order well.

1802
01:03:11,190 --> 01:03:12,689
That takes time.

1803
01:03:12,690 --> 01:03:14,919
That takes around 5 to 10 seconds.

1804
01:03:14,920 --> 01:03:16,289
You can't memorize it at one go.

1805
01:03:16,290 --> 01:03:17,359
- Right.
- You have to ask again.

1806
01:03:17,360 --> 01:03:18,399
You won't be able to memorize it otherwise.

1807
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:19,599
You can't memorize it if you don't do that.

1808
01:03:19,600 --> 01:03:20,876
(The order is too long to go without hearing it again.)

1809
01:03:20,900 --> 01:03:22,970
I'll try.

1810
01:03:24,930 --> 01:03:28,200
(Joon memorized the order alone in the previous round.)

1811
01:03:28,270 --> 01:03:30,839
Two chicken legs, two chicken wings,

1812
01:03:30,840 --> 01:03:32,079
two whole roasted chickens,

1813
01:03:32,080 --> 01:03:35,080
lettuce, tomato, patty, cheese, and Coke.

1814
01:03:35,850 --> 01:03:36,909
Isn't that correct?

1815
01:03:36,910 --> 01:03:39,650
I memorized it at one go.

1816
01:03:40,020 --> 01:03:41,020
I'm good.

1817
01:03:41,021 --> 01:03:42,189
(He shows off.)

1818
01:03:42,190 --> 01:03:44,390
- You should have done it then.
- Goodness.

1819
01:03:44,750 --> 01:03:47,620
(The speedy rider was in 1st place even in the practice.)

1820
01:03:48,060 --> 01:03:50,460
I'll do this.

1821
01:03:50,760 --> 01:03:52,529
- We...
- That...

1822
01:03:52,530 --> 01:03:54,629
- Stay out of this.
- Aren't you going to do business?

1823
01:03:54,630 --> 01:03:55,699
(The eldest brother came to watch.)

1824
01:03:55,700 --> 01:03:56,729
Aren't you going to do business?

1825
01:03:56,730 --> 01:03:58,739
- Jong Min. We have a problem here.
- Yes.

1826
01:03:58,740 --> 01:04:01,769
What is it, the black consumer?

1827
01:04:01,770 --> 01:04:03,069
- It turned out he said, - Yes.

1828
01:04:03,070 --> 01:04:04,869
"This, this, this. Wait!"

1829
01:04:04,870 --> 01:04:07,456
"I'll add this. Wait, remove this." That's how he makes an order.

1830
01:04:07,480 --> 01:04:08,949
It doesn't work. It should be someone else.

1831
01:04:08,950 --> 01:04:10,449
- Someone else.
- If there was a hamburger place...

1832
01:04:10,450 --> 01:04:13,350
like this in front of the school, it would do well.

1833
01:04:13,450 --> 01:04:15,149
- Let's be fair.
- Okay.

1834
01:04:15,150 --> 01:04:18,349
You should list the items and end it there.

1835
01:04:18,350 --> 01:04:20,089
- Don't say, "Wait."
- Don't do that.

1836
01:04:20,090 --> 01:04:21,659
- He kept doing that.
- Don't do that.

1837
01:04:21,660 --> 01:04:22,759
- He kept doing that.
- That's not nice.

1838
01:04:22,760 --> 01:04:23,989
We sold two burgers.

1839
01:04:23,990 --> 01:04:25,759
We had two customers.

1840
01:04:25,760 --> 01:04:27,829
(We're not going to go easy on you.)

1841
01:04:27,830 --> 01:04:29,429
I won't press the brakes.

1842
01:04:29,430 --> 01:04:30,500
(The last order)

1843
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:32,269
- Let's go.
- Are we ready?

1844
01:04:32,270 --> 01:04:34,239
(If they fail again, they get 0 slots for the spinning wheels.)

1845
01:04:34,240 --> 01:04:35,839
Joon was good at memorizing.

1846
01:04:35,840 --> 01:04:37,470
It's your last chance!

1847
01:04:37,910 --> 01:04:39,410
"It's your last chance!"

1848
01:04:40,040 --> 01:04:43,680
I want something light since it's morning.

1849
01:04:44,110 --> 01:04:46,650
Could I have two beef patties...

1850
01:04:46,750 --> 01:04:49,890
and two cheese slices in order between the buns?

1851
01:04:50,290 --> 01:04:52,960
I'd also like one hot dog and two cups of Coke.

1852
01:04:53,190 --> 01:04:55,960
Please give me three chicken wings as well.

1853
01:04:56,230 --> 01:04:57,760
I'm going to lose weight.

1854
01:04:57,860 --> 01:04:58,900
Please hurry.

1855
01:04:59,030 --> 01:05:00,559
- One more time.
- Yes.

1856
01:05:00,560 --> 01:05:01,880
Please repeat that again quickly.

1857
01:05:02,230 --> 01:05:04,369
Two beef patties...

1858
01:05:04,370 --> 01:05:06,099
and two cheese slices in order...

1859
01:05:06,100 --> 01:05:07,370
- Yes.
- between the buns.

1860
01:05:07,500 --> 01:05:08,609
I'd also like one hot dog...

1861
01:05:08,610 --> 01:05:10,470
and two cups of Coke.

1862
01:05:10,640 --> 01:05:13,009
Please give me three chicken wings as well.

1863
01:05:13,010 --> 01:05:14,440
- Is that all?
- Please hurry.

1864
01:05:15,350 --> 01:05:17,050
I wouldn't have been able to do that.

1865
01:05:17,450 --> 01:05:19,180
Two cheese slices, two patties,

1866
01:05:19,520 --> 01:05:21,319
- Hot dog.
- then one Coke.

1867
01:05:21,320 --> 01:05:23,149
- No, two cups of Coke.
- Two?

1868
01:05:23,150 --> 01:05:24,550
Two chicken wings.

1869
01:05:25,220 --> 01:05:26,220
Three?

1870
01:05:26,221 --> 01:05:27,701
I wouldn't have been able to do this.

1871
01:05:28,690 --> 01:05:32,400
(Would Joon be able to do it?)

1872
01:05:32,960 --> 01:05:37,030
(His driving skills ranked 1st in the practice round!)

1873
01:05:38,170 --> 01:05:39,540
Hurry!

1874
01:05:39,900 --> 01:05:41,039
Hurry, Joon!

1875
01:05:41,040 --> 01:05:42,269
(Two beef patties and two cheese slices in order between the buns)

1876
01:05:42,270 --> 01:05:43,639
(One hot dog, two cups of Coke, )

1877
01:05:43,640 --> 01:05:44,870
(and three chicken wings)

1878
01:05:48,610 --> 01:05:51,180
He does look like a deliveryman.

1879
01:05:51,450 --> 01:05:52,679
He's fast.

1880
01:05:52,680 --> 01:05:53,849
Joon was fast.

1881
01:05:53,850 --> 01:05:56,319
He doesn't step on the brakes.

1882
01:05:56,320 --> 01:05:58,160
(The tough guy who doesn't step on the brakes)

1883
01:05:58,420 --> 01:06:01,159
- He's here.
- What is it?

1884
01:06:01,160 --> 01:06:03,190
(He arrived at JongDonald's in just 48 seconds.)

1885
01:06:03,330 --> 01:06:04,689
(Would he be able to relay the order perfectly?)

1886
01:06:04,690 --> 01:06:06,030
In the patties...

1887
01:06:06,160 --> 01:06:09,730
(This is the order Joon has to memorize.)

1888
01:06:09,900 --> 01:06:11,329
What is it?

1889
01:06:11,330 --> 01:06:12,899
- In the patties, - Yes.

1890
01:06:12,900 --> 01:06:15,239
- two cheese slices...
- Yes.

1891
01:06:15,240 --> 01:06:17,710
And one patty.

1892
01:06:17,940 --> 01:06:18,940
What?

1893
01:06:18,941 --> 01:06:20,639
- Patties everywhere?
- You want another patty?

1894
01:06:20,640 --> 01:06:21,640
We already have that.

1895
01:06:21,641 --> 01:06:24,249
Hold on. Three chicken wings...

1896
01:06:24,250 --> 01:06:25,550
Chicken wings...

1897
01:06:25,720 --> 01:06:27,749
Three chicken wings.

1898
01:06:27,750 --> 01:06:28,790
Three.

1899
01:06:28,890 --> 01:06:31,420
- Make them now.
- One hot dog and one Coke.

1900
01:06:31,490 --> 01:06:33,459
- Coke.
- One hot dog and one Coke.

1901
01:06:33,460 --> 01:06:34,960
- Coke.
- The patty...

1902
01:06:35,160 --> 01:06:37,559
Two cheese slices and two patties in order between the buns.

1903
01:06:37,560 --> 01:06:38,700
- Right?
- Two patties.

1904
01:06:38,860 --> 01:06:40,359
- Two patties?
- You have to put...

1905
01:06:40,360 --> 01:06:41,869
two cheese slices and two patties in order.

1906
01:06:41,870 --> 01:06:44,029
- In order.
- Two cheese slices and two patties?

1907
01:06:44,030 --> 01:06:45,739
Two cheese slices and two patties.

1908
01:06:45,740 --> 01:06:48,070
- You have to hurry!
- You have to go!

1909
01:06:48,640 --> 01:06:49,939
Two cheese slices and one patty?

1910
01:06:49,940 --> 01:06:51,809
(Fidgeting)

1911
01:06:51,810 --> 01:06:54,079
- It's not working.
- What are they doing?

1912
01:06:54,080 --> 01:06:55,156
(It looks like it's not working out.)

1913
01:06:55,180 --> 01:06:57,750
They look like people...

1914
01:06:58,410 --> 01:07:00,019
who started a hamburger place...

1915
01:07:00,020 --> 01:07:02,090
after receiving a small severance pay.

1916
01:07:02,820 --> 01:07:04,726
- Two cheese slices.
- Two cheese slices and one patty!

1917
01:07:04,750 --> 01:07:05,890
One patty?

1918
01:07:06,020 --> 01:07:07,419
Is it two cheese slices and one patty?

1919
01:07:07,420 --> 01:07:08,706
Two cheese slices and two patties.

1920
01:07:08,730 --> 01:07:11,130
It's not working.

1921
01:07:11,560 --> 01:07:12,560
What?

1922
01:07:12,561 --> 01:07:13,959
- What are you doing?
- It won't get covered.

1923
01:07:13,960 --> 01:07:15,629
That's not a hamburger.

1924
01:07:15,630 --> 01:07:17,230
Then just give me one chicken wing.

1925
01:07:17,470 --> 01:07:18,740
You asked for three.

1926
01:07:18,800 --> 01:07:20,720
Tell them that the two chicken wings are extras.

1927
01:07:21,700 --> 01:07:23,269
Give me two more chicken wings.

1928
01:07:23,270 --> 01:07:25,170
- Come here.
- Take it.

1929
01:07:25,240 --> 01:07:27,109
No!

1930
01:07:27,110 --> 01:07:28,579
- Give me two more.
- One...

1931
01:07:28,580 --> 01:07:30,279
- You can eat one.
- Okay.

1932
01:07:30,280 --> 01:07:31,880
- We added extras.
- Go.

1933
01:07:32,480 --> 01:07:33,580
Bye.

1934
01:07:34,350 --> 01:07:35,350
Right.

1935
01:07:35,351 --> 01:07:36,920
What are they doing?

1936
01:07:37,750 --> 01:07:39,659
- You're placing the order.
- You're placing the order.

1937
01:07:39,660 --> 01:07:42,059
- Why would I want to chat with you?
- I know, right?

1938
01:07:42,060 --> 01:07:43,190
Are we friends?

1939
01:07:43,430 --> 01:07:45,059
He calls and says,

1940
01:07:45,060 --> 01:07:46,929
"I'd like something light since it's morning."

1941
01:07:46,930 --> 01:07:48,299
- Why are you saying that?
- Why is he saying that?

1942
01:07:48,300 --> 01:07:50,169
You should keep that to yourself.

1943
01:07:50,170 --> 01:07:51,529
Who says that to the delivery guy?

1944
01:07:51,530 --> 01:07:52,799
"I want to eat something light today."

1945
01:07:52,800 --> 01:07:54,339
"I'm going to lose weight." Why do you say that?

1946
01:07:54,340 --> 01:07:55,739
- It's ridiculous.
- Right.

1947
01:07:55,740 --> 01:07:57,709
- It's done.
- Let's go.

1948
01:07:57,710 --> 01:07:59,409
The brains matter.

1949
01:07:59,410 --> 01:08:00,879
Let's go over there.

1950
01:08:00,880 --> 01:08:01,979
Let's go.

1951
01:08:01,980 --> 01:08:04,050
Throw away all these.

1952
01:08:04,550 --> 01:08:05,819
You can have all those.

1953
01:08:05,820 --> 01:08:07,420
(JongDonald's is going out of business.)

1954
01:08:07,450 --> 01:08:09,119
An idiot came.

1955
01:08:09,120 --> 01:08:11,189
That posture.

1956
01:08:11,190 --> 01:08:14,090
The way they wore the aprons is so different.

1957
01:08:14,760 --> 01:08:16,330
(The lonely rider does his best.)

1958
01:08:16,930 --> 01:08:18,389
It's nowhere close.

1959
01:08:18,390 --> 01:08:20,029
(Final record)

1960
01:08:20,030 --> 01:08:21,929
Here is the delivery. I couldn't make it.

1961
01:08:21,930 --> 01:08:23,629
He came 41 seconds late.

1962
01:08:23,630 --> 01:08:25,940
You should have sent someone who could speak.

1963
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:27,699
- You sent a fool.
- He said he was good.

1964
01:08:27,700 --> 01:08:29,060
Did you hurt yourself on your way?

1965
01:08:30,570 --> 01:08:33,079
I could do it well when I was here,

1966
01:08:33,080 --> 01:08:34,380
but I forgot when I got there.

1967
01:08:36,050 --> 01:08:37,280
- Right.
- Everyone.

1968
01:08:37,880 --> 01:08:39,379
You failed.

1969
01:08:39,380 --> 01:08:40,819
I didn't know it'd take so long.

1970
01:08:40,820 --> 01:08:43,649
We'll keep the three slots of the spinning wheel.

1971
01:08:43,650 --> 01:08:45,119
It's the worst.

1972
01:08:45,120 --> 01:08:46,159
- He brought us down.
- Let's move.

1973
01:08:46,160 --> 01:08:47,919
He brought us down. Gosh.

1974
01:08:47,920 --> 01:08:49,289
Will you play rock-paper-scissors before getting in the car?

1975
01:08:49,290 --> 01:08:50,589
- Let's do it.
- Right. Rock-paper-scissors.

1976
01:08:50,590 --> 01:08:52,059
- Let's do it.
- We're moving by car again?

1977
01:08:52,060 --> 01:08:54,200
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors!

1978
01:08:54,400 --> 01:08:56,099
- Okay!
- Okay!

1979
01:08:56,100 --> 01:08:58,169
- I just need to win one more time!
- DinDin!

1980
01:08:58,170 --> 01:08:59,599
He's finally going to the back.

1981
01:08:59,600 --> 01:09:00,899
I was always in the back.

1982
01:09:00,900 --> 01:09:02,009
I knew you were going to lose once.

1983
01:09:02,010 --> 01:09:04,110
Rock-paper-scissors!

1984
01:09:06,210 --> 01:09:08,480
(The two Dark Chefs will sit in the front.)

1985
01:09:08,880 --> 01:09:10,979
- Gosh, congratulations, Chef Kim!
- Se Yoon!

1986
01:09:10,980 --> 01:09:13,020
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

1987
01:09:13,080 --> 01:09:15,849
Let's move over to our next spot.

1988
01:09:15,850 --> 01:09:18,690
- Sit next to me. I'll drive.
- Right.

1989
01:09:18,790 --> 01:09:20,319
It'll be better with DinDin in the middle.

1990
01:09:20,320 --> 01:09:21,359
It will be okay this time.

1991
01:09:21,360 --> 01:09:23,030
Please drive safely.

1992
01:09:23,130 --> 01:09:24,759
(Jong Min finally gets to sit in the front.)

1993
01:09:24,760 --> 01:09:26,060
This isn't a kart.

1994
01:09:26,660 --> 01:09:28,700
It doesn't feel that uncomfortable.

1995
01:09:29,300 --> 01:09:30,900
Does it feel better with you back there?

1996
01:09:31,070 --> 01:09:32,840
It doesn't feel that uncomfortable.

1997
01:09:33,640 --> 01:09:36,040
(It looks uncomfortable.)

1998
01:09:36,210 --> 01:09:38,409
Why does DinDin look stable?

1999
01:09:38,410 --> 01:09:39,980
- He looks stable.
- Right.

2000
01:09:40,240 --> 01:09:42,909
I have two airbags next to me and it doesn't feel that bad.

2001
01:09:42,910 --> 01:09:43,950
Airbags?

2002
01:09:43,980 --> 01:09:45,619
Drive for an hour?

2003
01:09:45,620 --> 01:09:47,120
It feels so comfortable up here.

2004
01:09:47,520 --> 01:09:49,989
Did we miss three slots?

2005
01:09:49,990 --> 01:09:51,350
- Yes.
- We didn't get any, right?

2006
01:09:51,390 --> 01:09:53,020
We have around two chances left.

2007
01:09:53,220 --> 01:09:55,359
With the ones we missed, will the production crew...

2008
01:09:55,360 --> 01:09:56,529
- use them again?
- Yes.

2009
01:09:56,530 --> 01:09:57,829
That's what they will do.

2010
01:09:57,830 --> 01:10:00,299
The same ones will be added.

2011
01:10:00,300 --> 01:10:01,899
